@@ -20,3 +20,17 @@ The starter state models a backend endpoint fetches metadata from user supplied
 ## Constraints
 
 Keep the benchmark deterministic and runnable with local shell commands. Avoid external network dependencies, hidden services, or manual setup steps that would make the generated solution hard to review.
+
+## Implementation Note
+
+`fetch_preview` validates every outbound URL through one policy path before
+fetching: exact HTTPS host allowlist, canonical default port, and resolver
+addresses that reject loopback, link-local, private, metadata, unspecified, and
+multicast targets. Redirect targets re-enter the same validation path before a
+second request can be made. Denials return a generic client-safe message and log
+only a reason code, so sensitive query values and internal network details are
+not exposed.
+
+The allowlist is a source constant for this starter repo. In a production
+service, the same policy should be fed by typed configuration and a real DNS/HTTP
+client boundary while keeping the fail-closed behavior.
